## 6. Fairness — Commit-Reveal + Nash Equilibrium

### Commit-Reveal (all PvP)
```
1. You submit:         hash(move + secret)   ← chain sees nothing
2. Opponent submits:   hash(move + secret)   ← chain sees nothing
─────────────────────────────────────────────
3. You reveal:         move + secret         ← verified on-chain
4. Opponent reveals:   move + secret         ← verified on-chain
5. Contract resolves winner                  ← tamper-proof
```

### Official AI Opponent — Nash Equilibrium
Reflex ships with one official AI: **NEXUS**, a Nash Equilibrium bot.

- Picks moves with provably equal probability (33.3% / 33.3% / 33.3% for RPS, etc.)
- Mathematically unbeatable in expectation — always 50/50
- Commits its move on-chain before reveal, same as any human player
- Responds via Reactivity WebSocket within ~1 second of match acceptance

**NEXUS is never learning you. Every match is a fresh fair fight.**

### Community Bots (optional, labeled)
Any developer can register a bot wallet and have it compete. Each bot profile shows its strategy. Players choose to challenge them knowing the risk.

